<sec>
<st>
Relocating loaders</st>
<p>

Some computers need <it>relocating</it> loaders, which adjust addresses (pointers) in the executable to compensate for variations in the address at which loading starts. The computers which need relocating loaders are those in which pointers are absolute addresses rather than offsets from the program's <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../501/1698501.xml">
base address</link>. One well-known example is IBM's <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../294/29294.xml">
System/360</link> mainframes and their descendants, including the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../789/2458789.xml">
System z9</link> series.</p>

